# Vouch — Product Specification & Build Document (v2)

## PURPOSE
This document is a complete product specification for building a working prototype of Vouch — a trust-based social platform where users post life questions and receive experience-based responses. The platform has a public global feed as the front door and opt-in trust groups as the retention and differentiation mechanic. Structured for Claude Code to implement as a Next.js application with Supabase backend.

---

## TECH STACK

- **Framework:** Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Realtime)
- **Deployment:** Vercel (frontend), Supabase (backend)
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (email magic link for MVP)
- **Notifications:** Email via connected email account

---

## CORE CONCEPT

**Tagline:** "In a world with a billion opinions, filter the ones that matter."

**Platform motivation (shown during onboarding):**
Every day, millions of people turn to the internet with real questions about their lives — career decisions, personal struggles, big transitions. They get anonymous hot takes, AI-generated content, and performative advice from strangers. Vouch is different. Here, people share real experiences from real lives. You start in an open community of genuine questions. Over time, you build trust circles — small groups of people whose judgment you actually value — so you can filter the signal from the noise on the questions that matter most.

