## FLOW 7: USER PROFILE

### URL: /profile/[id]

**Header section:**
- Display name, bio, avatar
- Join date
- Stats: "X questions asked · X experiences shared · X loops closed"

**Helpfulness indicator:**
Displayed below stats, only if the user has received ratings. Shows as a warm, non-numeric signal:

- 5+ ratings: "Helpful" (small badge)
- 15+ ratings: "Very helpful" (badge)
- 30+ ratings: "Highly valued" (badge)

Below the badge, a line: "Recognized as helpful by X people across Y conversations"

This gives enough signal for trust group discovery without creating a leaderboard. The thresholds and labels can be tuned post-launch based on actual distribution.

**Utility text:** *"A person's profile shows how they show up — the questions they ask, the experiences they share, and what others say about them."*

**Section: "What People Say"**
- If the user is in any trust groups, show vouch_context entries from group creators/members
- Each shows: Who said it + what they said + which group
- This section only appears if vouches exist

**Section: "Recent Activity"**
- Questions asked (with status: open/resolved)
- Responses shared (linked to parent question)
- Outcomes posted

**Section: "Add to Trust Group" (visible to other users viewing this profile)**
If the profile viewer has trust groups, show a button: **"Invite [Name] to a group"**
This links to the group invite flow with the person pre-filled. This is the key connection between helpfulness ratings and trust group growth — you read a helpful response, visit the profile, see the helpfulness badge, and invite them to your group.

**What this page does NOT show:**
- No follower/following count
- No exact helpfulness rating count on individual responses
- No engagement metrics
- No veiled questions the user asked
- No "times viewed"
- No ranking relative to other users

