## UI/UX DESIGN PRINCIPLES

### Visual Design
- Clean, minimal, warm. Think Apple Notes meets a thoughtful journal.
- White/off-white backgrounds. Warm accent color (teal or deep blue-green).
- Generous whitespace. No density optimization.
- Typography-first: 16px min body, 1.6 line height.
- No infinite scroll — paginated with "Load more" after 15 items.

### Contextual Utility Text
**Every page/feature has a brief line of text explaining what it's for and why it works this way.** This is a core design principle — the platform teaches its own culture through the interface. These texts are:
- Short (1-2 sentences)
- Warm and direct (not corporate)
- Focused on the user's benefit ("helps you...") not the platform's mechanics
- Muted in visual weight (smaller font, gray text) so they don't dominate

Examples already specified per flow above. Additional instances:

| Page | Utility Text |
|------|-------------|
| Global feed | "Real questions from the community. Respond with your experience, or ask your own." |
| Trust group feed | "Questions here are only visible to group members. A space for the questions that need a trusted audience." |
| Ask page | "The best questions are specific and honest. Share what you're actually trying to figure out." |
| Response form | "Respond with what you've actually been through. Specific experiences help more than general advice." |
| Profile page | "A person's profile shows how they show up — the questions they ask, the experiences they share, and what people say about them." |
| Notifications | "You'll only hear from us when something real happens." |
| Outcome page | "Closing the loop helps everyone — it shows what happened and lets you thank the people who showed up." |
| Create trust group | "A trust group is a small circle of people whose experience and judgment you value." |
| Onboarding | "In a world with a billion opinions, filter the ones that matter." |

### Anti-Patterns (Things to explicitly NOT build)
- No follower counts anywhere
- No public like/upvote counts ON INDIVIDUAL RESPONSE CARDS (helpfulness ratings accumulate on profiles, not on cards)
- No trending section
- No algorithmic feed ranking
- No infinite scroll
- No stories/ephemeral content
- No content recommendations
- No "who viewed your profile"
- No gamification (streaks, badges, levels) — the helpfulness tiers are NOT gamification; they are earned reputation signals with no streaks, no competition, no leaderboard
- No share-to-external-platform buttons
- No engagement metric dashboards
- No threading/reply-to-reply

